name: src/_apply.js
_apply
description:
Applies a given sequence (in the given order) of transpositions (given as
index tuples) to a given permutation. The permutation is modified in place.

params.name: sigma
params.description: The permutation to apply the transpositions to.

name: src/_bitreversal.js
_bitreversal
description: Fills an input array with the bitreversal permutation for input n items. The array is filled starting at index 0 and ending at index n-1. Note that n MUST be a power of 2.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the permutation, must be a power of 2.

name: src/_compose.js
_compose
description:
Compose two input permutations. The resulting permutation is output as an
iterator of indices instead of an array of indices.

unknown.tagValue: {Iterator} An iterator over the items of the resulting permutation.

return.description: An iterator over the items of the resulting permutation.

name: src/_copy.js
_copy
description: Copy an input permutation to an output array.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the input permutation to copy.

name: src/_cycles.js
_cycles
description: Computes a {@link https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation#Cycle_notation cycle decomposition} of an input permutation. This algorithm is deterministic; the algorithm will procedes in a sequential manner, first yielding the cycle containing the first (in input order) index of the permutation, then yielding the cycle containing the first (in input order) index of the permutation that is not in the first cycle, etc. The output is in the form of an iterator over cycles [a, [b, c, ...]] where a is the first element of the cycle and the list [b, c, ...] contains the second, third, etc. elements of the cycle. The algorithm uses an helper array to remember which elements have already been encountered.

name: src/_identity.js
_identity
description: Fills an input array with the identity permutation on input n elements.

params.name: n
params.description: The size to use for the permutation.

name: src/_invert.js
_invert
description: Fills an input array with the inverse rho of the input permutation sigma, that is, the permutation such that compose(rho, sigma) returns identity(sigma.length).

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the input permutation.

params.name: tau
params.description: The array where to put the inverse of the input permutation.

name: src/_invertcycles.js
_invertcycles
description: No idea what this does. Probably inverts the cycles of a given permutation.

name: src/_itranspositions.js
_itranspositions
description: Really no idead what this does.

name: src/_next.js
_next
description:
Updates the input permutation to the next one. Returns true unless the input
permutation is the last for its elements. In that case, the input permutation
remains untouched.

unknown.tagValue:
{Boolean} Whether the input permutation is
<underline>NOT</underline> the last for its elements.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the input permutation.

return.description:
Whether the input permutation is
<underline>NOT</underline> the last for its elements.

name: src/_permutations.js
_permutations
description:
Yields all permutations starting from a given one and ending at the last
permutation.

unknown.tagValue:
{Iterator} Iterator over all permutations between the starting one
and the last permutation on its elements.

return.description:
Iterator over all permutations between the starting one
and the last permutation on its elements.

name: src/_reverse.js
_reverse
description: Reverses input permutation in place from input index i (include) to input index j (excluded).

name: src/_transpose.js
_transpose
description: Transpose elements of input index a and b in the input permutation.

name: src/_transposition.js
_transposition
description: Helper method for {@link transposition}. Transposes a with b in sigma provided sigma[a] === a and sigma[b] === b.

name: src/_transpositions.js
_transpositions
description:
Computes the transposition decomposition of some permutation given its cycle
decomposition.

unknown.tagValue:
{Iterator} The transposition decomposition of the permutation
defined by the input cycles.

params.name: cycles
params.description: The cycle decomposition of some permutation.

return.description:
The transposition decomposition of the permutation
defined by the input cycles.

name: src/_used.js
_used
description: For a given size n, fills an input array with false. Starting at index 0, ending at index n-1. This array is used as a helper in other function. For example, for computing the cycle decomposition of an input permutation (see {@link _cycles}, {@link cycles}).

name: src/apply.js
apply
description: Apply a given sequence (in the given order) of transpositions (given as index tuples) to the identity permutation over input n elements.

params.name: n
params.description:
The size of the identity permutation to apply the transpositions
to.

name: src/bitreversal.js
bitreversal
description: Returns a newly allocated array containing the bitreversal permutation for input n items. Note that n MUST be a power of 2.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the permutation, must be a power of 2.

name: src/compose.js
compose
description:
Compose two input permutations. The resulting permutation is output as an
array of indices.

unknown.tagValue: {Array} The resulting permutation as an array.

return.description: The resulting permutation as an array.

name: src/copy.js
copy
description: Make a copy of the input permutation.

name: src/cycles.js
cycles

Computes the cycle decomposition of the input permutation.

identity

name: src/itranspositions.js
itranspositions
description: Really no idead what this does, see also {@link _itranspositions}.

name: src/next.js
next
description:
Computes the permutation that follows the input permutation. If the input
permutation is the last for its elements, return the first for its elements.
The input permutation is not altered.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the permutation to allocate.

permutations

unknown.tagValue: {Iterator} Iterator that yields all permutations on n elements.

reverse

name: src/reversed.js
reversed
description: Outputs a new permutation that is the reverse of the input permutation.

unknown.tagValue: {Array} The reverse of the input permutation.

return.description: The reverse of the input permutation.

name: src/transpose.js
transpose
description:
Creates a copy of the input permutation, applies an input transpose,
then returns the result.

params.name: a
params.description: The first index of the transpose.

params.name: b
params.description: The second index of the transpose.

transposition

params.description: The size of the permutation to output.

Computes the transposition decomposition of the input permutation as an
Iterator.

used

unknown.tagValue: {Array} The helper array of prescribed size.
